From Marc WANDSCHNEIDER Subject Re Know anything about EISA In article Bing Ho writes I read about the development of EISA some time ago but dismissed it in light of the intense interest in VESA and However I recently was disheartened to hear that ISA cannot address more than of RAM a limit that too many of us will hit all too I recall that EISA will support bit transfer among other Is there such a standard being developed Very possibly but if it's still going to be backwards compatible with the ISA bus it's going to be the same tripe that the current EISA implementation really From what I've seen the PCI bus will just be a new intelligent bus ie bus controller takes care of interrupts and the like not Hopefully it'll get somewhere up there with the AMIGA Zorro III VL Bus is a bit too much of a hack for my Toodlepip Marc '